Cody continued for the door, and Lulu once again sidled out of the way at the last moment and whined. “Now, now, that's not going to get you anywhere,” Cody said reprovingly. He thought about it for a moment. “Well, if you continued doing it long enough, I'd probably head down the stairs just to make you stop.” He looked down at the dog. “It's a good thing you don't understand a word I'm saying.”
